      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BONDI QUEEN (7) has taken a while to get off the mark but this campaign seems to have been about getting her over ground and if last start is anything to go by that's where her future lies. Stepped up to 1435m here last time and ran away with a six-length win and looks ideally suited at the mile now. Can go on with it. CAPRICORN MAN (2) was run over in the Derby Cup over a little further last time, but the start prior gave a huge sight here and was nabbed on the line. Take catching again. SUCCESS PLAY (3) is a handy type fitter for two runs for the new yard. Looks ideally placed at the mile now and best figures stack up. LUCKY LANDING (4) was in traffic last time and gets a chance to atone. SHOULDER PATCH (8) is better drawn and looks hard to beat in this line-up.",
